    "These projections are then subsequently processed to achieve place recognition.",
    "In this section, we discuss the projection-based methods by dividing them into three categories: 2D planes based methods, 2D image-based methods, and bird-eye view-based methods.",
    "The 2D planes based 3D-PCPR methods involve an initial step of projecting the raw 3D point cloud onto a 2D representation which is then utilized for subsequent place recognition tasks.",
    "A pioneering approach in this domain is M2DP (He et al. 2016), which projects a 3D point cloud onto a sequence of 2D planes that capture various viewpoints of the cloud.",
    "By characterizing the point projections, M2DP extracts multiple density distributions or signatures from a single point cloud."
  ],
